# Toronto Rising ‚Äî object-hosted script bundling (mandatory)

**Object scripts are bundled per object and sent on every Save & Play.** A single careless `require()` on an object entry (dice bag, CSHEET page, signal candle, NPC board, tarot button, soundscape emitter, ‚Ä¶) duplicates that module tree **once per object** ‚Äî often tens of copies. This can **break Save & Play** (huge payload, TTS reload abort, extension `Unexpected end of JSON input` on port 39998) even when Global-only changes are small.

Agents must treat object-script `require()` as **high risk** ‚Äî on par with Lua local function order.

## Scope ‚Äî what counts as ‚Äúobject-hosted‚Äù

Scripts attached to table objects (stubs under `.tts/objects/` ‚Üí `objects/*.ttslua`, `ui/ui_csheet*.ttslua`, `ui/ui_signal_candle.ttslua`, `ui/ui_tarot_button.ttslua`, `core/soundscape_emitter_object.ttslua`, etc.). Each runs in a **separate Lua VM** from Global; luabundle inlines the full `require()` graph into **that object's** bundled script.

Global / HUD paths (`core/global_script.ttslua`, storyteller XmlUI) are different ‚Äî one bundle, acceptable to pull the game stack.

## The rule

1. **Never** `require("core.*")` from object scripts (state, sync, roll_controller, npcs, ‚Ä¶).
2. **Never** `require` ‚Äúkitchen sink‚Äù libs from objects: `lib.constants`, `lib.util`, `lib.pcs_data`, `lib.pc_stats`, `lib.object_positions` (use **`lib.object_positions_object`**), or any module whose dependency graph reaches `core.*`.
3. **Import piecemeal only** ‚Äî object-purpose modules designed to stay thin (`lib.dice_kinds`, `lib.guids`, `lib.csheet_util`, `lib.blood_potency_constants`, ‚Ä¶). If you need game state or orchestration, add a **`Global.call("Global‚Ä¶")`** entry in `core/global_script.ttslua` and keep the object stub dumb.
4. **Do not** `require` a Global module ‚Äújust for one helper‚Äù if that module pulls `core.state` or similar ‚Äî route through Global instead (see TOR-262 dice bag incident below).
5. **Lazy `require` inside functions** may still be bundled on some paths; prefer **top-level** requires only of whitelisted thin modules, or Global.call.
6. Before finishing any object-script change: mentally multiply bundle size by **number of objects** with that stub (e.g. **22** dice bags, **~37** CSHEET pages).

## Approved patterns

| Need | Object script | Global |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Tier C world mutation | `Global.call("GlobalRequireHostForWorldMutation", ‚Ä¶)` | Host-guarded `Global*` callee |
| Roll / tray / game state | `Global.call("GlobalGetPcRollTrayYOffset", ‚Ä¶)` etc. | `require` domain modules |
| NPC gameboard Apply | `Global.call("GlobalGameboardApply", ‚Ä¶)` | `core.npc_gameboard` |
| Tarot toggle | `lib.tarot_toggle` + **`lib.object_positions_object`** only | full `lib.object_positions` |
| CSHEET UI | `ui.ui_csheet` / `ui.ui_csheet_pageN` thin chain | sheet collect, sync |

Canonical inventory: [`.dev/TTS_BUNDLING_SETUP.md`](../../.dev/TTS_BUNDLING_SETUP.md) ¬ß Character sheet pages / NPC gameboard objects.

## Incident ‚Äî TOR-262 dice bags (2026-07-03)

`objects/dice_bag.ttslua` gained `require("lib.pc_roll_tray_lower")`, which pulls `core.state` ‚Üí **~84 modules, ~2.6 MB per bag** √ó 22 bags ‚âà **+56 MB** Save & Play payload. Fix: `GlobalGetPcRollTrayYOffset` via `Global.call`; bags back to **~54 KB** (3 modules).

## Agent checklist (before marking object-script work done)

1. List **every new or changed `require()`** in object entry files you touched.
2. Walk the dependency graph ‚Äî grep the required file for `require("core.` and `require("lib.constants")`.
3. If any heavy module appears, **stop** and switch to Global.call or a thinner object-only module.
4. Run `npm run tts-save:measure-bundles` when CSHEET/NPC/dice stubs changed; flag any object bundle with `core.*` or `lib.constants` as regression.
5. After substantive object-script edits, **Save & Play once** ‚Äî bundle bloat does not show in `npm run build`.

## Symptom ‚Üí likely cause

| Symptom | Likely cause |
| --- | --- |
| Save & Play hangs on ‚ÄúSending Scripts‚Äù; Extension Host `Unexpected end of JSON input` on 39998 | Payload too large or TTS reload aborted; check object bundles for `core.*` |
| `Tried to require "core.foo", but no such module has been registered` in object VM | Object script required Global-only module at runtime |
| One object type fine, many copies break send | Same `require()` duplicated per object (dice bags, CSHEET pages) |
